    welcomeTitle: '# Welcome to CAScad',
    welcomeBody: '## Cell Types\n\n**Math cells** ‚Äî Type mathematics visually using MathLive. Expressions are automatically converted to Giac syntax and evaluated. Try the *Arithmetic*, *Algebra*, or *Linear Algebra* examples.\n\n**GIAC cells** ‚Äî Enter raw Giac CAS syntax directly, for variable assignments (`:=`), programming constructs, or advanced commands. See the *Programming* example.\n\n**Text cells** ‚Äî Write documentation with Markdown and LaTeX: inline $E = mc^2$ and display mode:\n\n$$\\int_0^\\infty e^{-x}\\,dx = 1$$\n\nClick the **type badge** (Math / GIAC / Text) on any cell to change its type.\n\n## Running Cells\n\n- **Enter** ‚Äî Run the current cell (Math visual mode only)\n- **Shift + Enter** ‚Äî Run the current cell (all cell types)\n- **Ctrl + Enter** ‚Äî Run and insert a new cell below\n- **‚ñ∂ Run all** ‚Äî Execute all cells at once\n\nIn **GIAC** and **Text** cells, Enter inserts a new line as usual.\n\n## Reactive Mode\n\nToggle **Reactive** to create live notebooks. Define variables with `:=` and reference them in downstream cells ‚Äî changes propagate automatically. See the *Reactive Variables* and *Quadratic Equation* examples.\n\n## Plots & Visualization\n\nGiac supports rich 2D and 3D plotting:\n\n- **2D plots**: `plot(sin(x), x)` ‚Äî see *Plots & Visualization*\n- **3D surfaces**: see *3D Surface*, *3D Parametric Surface*\n- **3D curves**: see *3D Curve (Helix)*\n- **Vector fields**: see *3D Vector Field*\n- **Interactive sliders**: real-time parameter control ‚Äî see *Amplitude Modulation*, *Fourier Series*, *Quadratic Equation*\n\n## Command Help\n\nGet documentation for any Giac command:\n\n- **help(command)** or **?command** ‚Äî Display help with description, syntax, examples, and related commands\n- **help()** ‚Äî General help overview\n- Click the **?** icon in the Commands menu for quick access\n\nHelp is available in multiple languages and supports case-insensitive lookup.\n\n## Command Discovery\n\nExplore and search the command library from any GIAC cell:\n\n- **search_commands("sin")** ‚Äî Find commands by name (prefix or regex)\n- **search_commands_by_description("matrix")** ‚Äî Search descriptions for keywords\n- **list_commands()** ‚Äî List all available commands\n- **help_count()** ‚Äî Show the total number of commands\n- **list_categories()** ‚Äî Browse command categories\n- **commands_in_category("trigonometry")** ‚Äî List commands in a category\n- **command_info("solve")** ‚Äî Show name, category, description, and syntax\n- **suggest_commands("factr")** ‚Äî Find similar commands (fuzzy matching)\n\nResults are interactive ‚Äî click any command name to view its full documentation.\n\n## Cell Controls\n\n- **Hide/Show** code (Ctrl+Shift+H) ‚Äî output-only display\n- **Disable/Enable** cell (Ctrl+Shift+D) ‚Äî skip during execution\n- **Lock/Unlock** cell (Ctrl+Shift+L) ‚Äî prevent editing\n- **Report view** (Ctrl+Shift+R) ‚Äî clean presentation mode\n- Drag the handle to **reorder** cells\n\n## Import, Export & Sharing\n\n- **üíæ Export** ‚Äî Save your notebook as a JSON file\n- **üìÇ Import** ‚Äî Load a previously saved notebook\n- **üì§ Share** ‚Äî Share via link, QR code, or social platforms\n- URL sharing with optional password encryption\n\n## Examples\n\nClick **üìö Examples** to explore 21 ready-made notebooks covering arithmetic, algebra, calculus, Fourier series, linear algebra, 3D visualization, physics, signal processing, interactive sliders, and more.',
